consume

public Boolean consume(Instance<Boolean> instance)
Description copied from interface: InstanceConsumer
Consume the instance and return the label assigned to the instance. If the consumer does not assign labels to instances (e.g. a training data consumer), this method should return null.

Parameters:
instance - The instance (features and label) to be consumed.
Returns:
The assigned label, or null if a label was not assigned.
